<title>USA: Santa Cruz sets additional stock buybacks.</title>
<headline>Santa Cruz sets additional stock buybacks.</headline>
<dateline>SANTA CRUZ, Calif 1997-06-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>Santa Cruz Opetation Inc said on Wednesday its directors  authorized the repurchase of up to an additional two million common shares on the open market or through privately negotiated transactions.</p>
<p>Spokesman John Nesbett said that this amount would be in addition to the five percent of the company's stock it said it would repurchase last August.</p>
<p>He was unable to say how many shares had been repurchased since then.</p>
<p>At that time, the company had nearly 39.4 million shares outstanding. Standard &amp; Poor's Marketscope now shows it with 36.6 million outstanding as of December 31.</p>
<p>((-- New York Newsdesk 212-859-1610.))</p>
